                <h1>How to Set a Desktop Background for All Users</h1>
                <p>Setting a desktop background for all users on a Windows system can enhance productivity and create a cohesive look. To do this, use Group Policy Editor (for Windows Pro) or modify the registry for other editions. By specifying a wallpaper file path, every user will automatically see the same background upon login, ensuring a uniform visual experience.</p>
